javaslang.algebra

Interface HigherKinded<T,TYPE extends HigherKinded<?,TYPE>>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - component type of the type to be constructed
    TYPE - the container type, i.e. the type to be constructed.
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Arbitrary<T>, CheckedMonad<T,M>, Gen<T>, List<T>, Monad<T,M>, Option<T>, Seq<T>, Stream<T>, Traversable<T>, Try<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Either.LeftProjection, Either.RightProjection, Failure, List.AbstractList, List.Cons, List.Nil, None, Some, Stream.AbstractStream, Stream.Cons, Stream.Deferred, Stream.Nil, Success

    public interface HigherKinded<T,TYPE extends HigherKinded<?,TYPE>>

    The HigherKinded type declares a generic type constructor, which consists of on component type and one container type. Subtypes of HigherKinded are expected to be of type TYPE.

    HigherKinded is used to approximately simulate higher-kinded/higher-order types, which cannot be expressed with Java.

    See also
    • Generics of a Higher Kind (Moors, Piessens, Odersky)
    • Kind (type theory) (wikipedia)
    • Type constructor (wikipedia)
    Since:
    1.1.0
